title: Blowin' in the Wind
lyrics:
How many roads must a man walk down
Before you call him a man?
How many seas must a white dove sail
Before she sleeps in the sand?
Yes, and how many times must the cannonballs fly
Before they're forever banned?
The answer, my friend, is blowin' in the wind
The answer is blowin' in the wind

title: The Sound of Silence
lyrics:
Hello darkness, my old friend
I've come to talk with you again
Because a vision softly creeping
Left its seeds while I was sleeping
And the vision that was planted in my brain
Still remains
Within the sound of silence

title: Hallelujah
lyrics:
Now I've heard there was a secret chord
That David played, and it pleased the Lord
But you don't really care for music, do you?
It goes like this, the fourth, the fifth
The minor fall, the major lift
The baffled king composing Hallelujah
Hallelujah, Hallelujah
Hallelujah, Hallelujah

title: Ho Hey
lyrics:
I belong with you, you belong with me
You're my sweetheart
I belong with you, you belong with me
You're my sweet (Ho!)
(Hey!)
(Ho!)
(Hey!)

title: Big Yellow Taxi
lyrics:
They paved paradise and put up a parking lot
With a pink hotel, a boutique, and a swinging hot spot
Don't it always seem to go
That you don't know what you've got 'til it's gone
They paved paradise and put up a parking lot

title: If I Had a Hammer (The Hammer Song)
lyrics:
If I had a hammer
I'd hammer in the morning
I'd hammer in the evening
All over this land
I'd hammer out danger
I'd hammer out a warning
I'd hammer out love between my brothers and my sisters
All over this land

title: This Land Is Your Land
lyrics:
This land is your land, this land is my land
From California to the New York island
From the redwood forest to the Gulf Stream waters
This land was made for you and me

title: Where Have All the Flowers Gone?
lyrics:
Where have all the flowers gone? Long time passing
Where have all the flowers gone? Long time ago
Where have all the flowers gone? Young girls have picked them, every one
Oh, when will they ever learn? Oh, when will they ever learn?

title: American Pie
lyrics:
Bye, bye Miss American Pie
Drove my Chevy to the levee but the levee was dry
And them good old boys were drinkin' whiskey and rye
Singin' this'll be the day that I die
This'll be the day that I die

title: Cat's in the Cradle
lyrics:
And the cat's in the cradle and the silver spoon
Little boy blue and the man in the moon
'When you comin' home, dad?' 'I don't know when'
But we'll get together then
You know we'll have a good time then

title: Both Sides, Now
lyrics:
I've looked at clouds from both sides now
From up and down, and still somehow
It's cloud illusions I recall
I really don't know clouds at all

chord_progression.main: F - C/E - Dm - C - Bb - F

title: Puff, the Magic Dragon
lyrics:
Puff, the magic dragon lived by the sea
And frolicked in the autumn mist in a land called Honahlee
Little Jackie Paper loved that rascal Puff
And brought him strings and sealing wax and other fancy stuff

title: The Times They Are A-Changin'
lyrics:
Come gather 'round people
Wherever you roam
And admit that the waters
Around you have grown
And accept it that soon
You'll be drenched to the bone
If your time to you is worth savin'
Then you better start swimmin' or you'll sink like a stone
For the times they are a-changin'

title: The Boxer
lyrics:
I am just a poor boy
Though my story's seldom told
I have squandered my resistance
For a pocketful of mumbles, such are promises
All lies and jest
Still, a man hears what he wants to hear
And disregards the rest

title: Suzanne
lyrics:
Suzanne takes you down to her place near the river
You can hear the boats go by, you can spend the night beside her
And you know that she's half-crazy but that's why you want to be there
And she feeds you tea and oranges that come all the way from China

title: Tom Dooley
lyrics:
Hang down your head, Tom Dooley
Hang down your head and cry
Hang down your head, Tom Dooley
Poor boy, you're bound to die

title: Leaving on a Jet Plane
lyrics:
So kiss me and smile for me
Tell me that you'll wait for me
Hold me like you'll never let me go
'Cause I'm leavin' on a jet plane
Don't know when I'll be back again
Oh, babe, I hate to go

title: Little Boxes
lyrics:
Little boxes on the hillside
Little boxes made of ticky-tacky
Little boxes on the hillside
Little boxes all the same
There's a green one and a pink one
And a blue one and a yellow one
And they're all made out of ticky-tacky
And they all look just the same

title: For What It's Worth
lyrics:
There's somethin' happenin' here
What it is ain't exactly clear
There's a man with a gun over there
Tellin' me I got to beware
I think it's time we stop
Children, what's that sound?
Everybody look what's goin' down

title: Landslide
lyrics:
Well, I've been afraid of changin'
'Cause I've built my life around you
But time makes you bolder
Even children get older
And I'm gettin' older too

title: Heart of Gold
lyrics:
I want to live, I want to give
I've been a miner for a heart of gold
It's these expressions I never give
That keep me searchin' for a heart of gold
And I'm gettin' old

title: Case of You
lyrics:
Oh, I could drink a case of you, darling
And I would still be on my feet
Oh, I would still be on my feet

title: Me and Bobby McGee
lyrics:
Freedom's just another word for nothin' left to lose
Nothin', don't mean nothin', hon', if it ain't free
And feelin' good was easy, Lord, when he sang the blues
You know, feelin' good was good enough for me
Good enough for me and my Bobby McGee

title: California Dreamin'
lyrics:
All the leaves are brown and the sky is gray
I've been for a walk on a winter's day
I'd be safe and warm if I was in L.A.
California dreamin' on such a winter's day

title: Early Morning Rain
lyrics:
In the early mornin' rain
With a dollar in my hand
And an aching in my heart
And my pockets full of sand
I'm a long way from home
And I miss my loved one so
In the early mornin' rain
With no place to go

title: Vincent
lyrics:
Starry, starry night
Paint your palette blue and gray
Look out on a summer's day
With eyes that know the darkness in my soul
Shadows on the hills
Sketch the trees and the daffodils
Catch the breeze and the winter chills
In colors on the snowy linen land

title: Like a Rolling Stone
lyrics:
How does it feel
How does it feel
To be on your own
With no direction home
Like a complete unknown
Like a rolling stone?

title: Homeward Bound
lyrics:
Homeward bound, I wish I was homeward bound
Home, where my thought's escaping
Home, where my music's playing
Home, where my love lies waiting silently for me

title: Turn! Turn! Turn! (To Everything There Is a Season)
lyrics:
To everything, turn, turn, turn
There is a season, turn, turn, turn
And a time to every purpose under heaven
A time to be born, a time to die
A time to plant, a time to reap
A time to kill, a time to heal
A time to laugh, a time to weep

title: The Weight
lyrics:
Take a load off, Fanny
Take a load for free
Take a load off, Fanny
And you put the load right on me

title: First Day of My Life
lyrics:
This is the first day of my life
I'm glad I didn't die before I met you
But now I don't care, I could go anywhere with you
And I'd probably be happy

title: If I Were a Carpenter
lyrics:
If I were a carpenter
And you were a lady
Would you marry me anyway?
Would you have my baby?

title: A Horse with No Name
lyrics:
I've been through the desert on a horse with no name
It felt good to be out of the rain
In the desert, you can't remember your name
'Cause there ain't no one for to give you no pain

title: Urge for Going
lyrics:
I get the urge for going
When the meadow grass is turning brown
And summertime is falling down
And winter is closing in

title: Mr. Tambourine Man
lyrics:
Hey, Mr. Tambourine Man, play a song for me
I'm not sleepy and there is no place I'm going to
Hey, Mr. Tambourine Man, play a song for me
In the jingle jangle morning I'll come followin' you

title: The Night They Drove Old Dixie Down
lyrics:
Virgil Caine is the name, and I served on the Danville train
'Til Stoneman's cavalry came and tore up the tracks again
In the winter of '65, we were hungry, just barely alive
By May the tenth, Richmond had fell
It's a time I remember, oh so well

title: Good Riddance (Time of Your Life)
lyrics:
It's something unpredictable, but in the end it's right
I hope you had the time of your life

title: Gentle on My Mind
lyrics:
It's knowing that your door is always open
And your path is free to walk
That makes me tend to leave my sleeping bag
Rolled up and stashed behind your couch

title: Pink Moon
lyrics:
I saw it written and I saw it say
Pink moon is on its way
And none of you stand so tall
Pink moon gonna get ye all
